        "details": {
            "description": "<p>A forest of fiendish trees swing their branches and shift their roots to bludgeon and trip creatures in the tainted grove (area <strong>A21</strong>).</p>",
            "disable": "<p>@Check[type:survival|dc:22|name:Find a Safe Location|traits:hazard,complex,environmental] (trained) to find a location the trees can't reach or @Check[type:religion|dc:24|name:Cast Out the Fiendish Energy|traits:hazard,complex,environmental] to recite a prayer that temporarily casts out the fiendish energy inside a single tree in the grove, disabling it for 1 minute. A disabled or destroyed tree creates a 5‑foot‑square area in the grove that's safe from this hazard.</p>",
            "isComplex": true,
            "level": {
                "value": 4
            },
            "reset": "<p>The Abyss-warped trees cease moving 1 minute after no living creatures are in the tainted grove. They reset immediately. A disabled tree reanimates after 1 minute. A destroyed tree regrows after 1 month.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(4 actions) The Abyss‑warped trees use their first action each round to lash their roots; each creature in the tainted grove must succeed at a @Check[type:reflex|dc:21|traits:hazard,complex,environmental] save or fall @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Prone]. The Abyss‑warped trees use their second, third, and fourth actions to make branch Strikes against up to three different creatures in the tainted grove.</p>",
